      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sessions): honor explicit default model pins",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Persist explicit user selections of the configured default model as exact session model pins instead of clearing them as if they were unpinned defaults.\n- Keep `/model default`, `session_status(model=default)`, and `sessions.patch model:null` as the explicit clear/unpin paths.\n- Carry the exact selection through reply, queued-run, agent-command, reset, status, and sessions.patch paths so channel/parent/config fallback policy cannot silently replace user intent.\n\n## Verification\nBehavior addressed: Explicit `/model <configured default>` selections no longer lose user intent just because they match the configured primary; fallback policy treats them as strict user session selections, while `/model default` still clears back to unpinned behavior.\nReal environment tested: local Codex worktree on beatrice.local, branch commit 87986ba3bfb7b6948ef4ce9fa5c9bc81cc7a603b atop upstream/main f2365053d330b100c024bdbe9159ea824b1d6243.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/sessions/reset-preserved-selection.test.ts src/sessions/model-overrides.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/model-selection.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/directive-handling.model.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.media-only.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.fast-path.test.ts src/agents/agent-command.live-model-switch.test.ts src/gateway/sessions-patch.test.ts src/commands/status.summary.test.ts src/status/status-message.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.session-status.test.ts src/auto-reply/status.test.ts src/commands/status.command-sections.test.ts`; `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/sessions/model-overrides.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/directive-handling.model.test.ts src/gateway/sessions-patch.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts src/agents/agent-command.live-model-switch.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.fast-path.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.media-only.test.ts src/config/sessions/reset-preserved-selection.test.ts src/auto-reply/status.test.ts src/commands/status.command-sections.test.ts`; `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/session-reset-model.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts src/gateway/server.sessions.reset-models.test.ts src/commands/status.summary.test.ts`; `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --write --threads=1 ...`; `git diff --check upstream/main..HEAD`; `codex review --base upstream/main`\nEvidence after fix: 18 Vitest files passed, 708 tests passed; final review subset passed 13 files / 538 tests plus reset/status follow-up coverage; diff check passed; branch review was clean.\nObserved result after fix: Explicit configured-default selections persist provider/model/source as user session overrides, survive resets, suppress configured/channel/parent fallback policy, and prevent fallback persistence from replacing user intent; `/model default` clears the override for unpinned behavior.\nWhat was not tested: Live Telegram/OpenAI provider turn with production credentials was not run; no live runtime files or LaunchAgent state were modified.\n",
